          <!-- Best Practices -->
          <div class="doc-section">
            <h2 id="detailed-guidelines" class="doc-section-title">Best Practices</h2>
            <p class="doc-section-subtitle">Visual and interaction guidelines to ensure icon buttons are effective, scalable, and accessible.</p>
            <div class="do-dont-grid">
              <div class="do-card"><span class="card-label">Do</span>
                <ul class="doc-list" style="border: none; background: transparent; padding: 0;">
                  <li style="border: none; background: transparent; padding-left: 20px;"><strong>Always provide an aria-label</strong> that describes the action, not the icon (e.g., "Delete item" not "Trash icon").</li>
                  <li style="border: none; background: transparent; padding-left: 20px;"><strong>Use universally recognized icons</strong> (close, add, edit, delete) to ensure immediate comprehension.</li>
                  <li style="border: none; background: transparent; padding-left: 20px;"><strong>Use tooltips</strong> to show the action label on hover for sighted users.</li>
                  <li style="border: none; background: transparent; padding-left: 20px;"><strong>Match icon button type</strong> to the Button type used nearby for visual consistency.</li>
                  <li style="border: none; background: transparent; padding-left: 20px;"><strong>Use circle shape</strong> for FAB-style (floating action button) actions.</li>
                </ul>
              </div>
              <div class="dont-card"><span class="card-label">Don't</span>
                <ul class="doc-list" style="border: none; background: transparent; padding: 0;">
                  <li style="border: none; background: transparent; padding-left: 20px;"><strong>Don't use for ambiguous actions</strong> without a tooltip to clarify the intent.</li>
                  <li style="border: none; background: transparent; padding-left: 20px;"><strong>Don't use when action needs text</strong> -- use a full Button component instead.</li>
                  <li style="border: none; background: transparent; padding-left: 20px;"><strong>Don't mix shapes</strong> in the same toolbar (square and circle).</li>
                  <li style="border: none; background: transparent; padding-left: 20px;"><strong>Don't use danger type</strong> for non-destructive actions.</li>
                  <li style="border: none; background: transparent; padding-left: 20px;"><strong>Don't disable without reason</strong> -- provide explanation via tooltip.</li>
                </ul>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

